                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="1ra" to="1va"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Prayer dedicated to Jesus Christ referring to His passion. The prayer is incomplete at the beginning.  
                              At the end of the text there is a brief supplication, asking for fogivness of sins for Śarṣa Yoḥannǝs.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"><gap reason="omitted"/> ያተ፡ እንግድዓከኒ፡ ቅንው፡ ምስለ፡ መስቀል፡ <!--ACHTUNG! -->
                              ዘ፩፡ ቀናት፡ ዘውፅአ፡ እንተ፡ ዘባንከ፡ አእጋሪከኒ፡ ቅንዋት፡ እንዘ፡ ያስተጣግዑ፡ ፩ደ፡ ምስለ፡ ካልኡ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="149va" to="150rb"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText"><title ref="LIT5627NagaraArestaAemro"/></desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ለ፬ዘይቤ፡ ልባዌ፡ አንብቦ፡ ዝማሬ፡ ጣዕመ፡ ዝማሬ፨
                              ለ፫ዘይቤ፡ አንብዕ፡ ኵነኒ፡ ዑቃቢ፡ ፍቅረ፡ ደቂቀ፡ እጓለ፡ እምሕያው፡ ሁሰት። ወበውስቴቱ፡ ይትኀብኡ፡ ፫ዘይቤ፡
                              ንጽሐ፡ ሥጋ፡ ንጽሐ፡ ሕሊና፡ ንጽሮ። ምስለ፡ ፲ዘይቤ፡ እምልባዌ፡ እስከ፡ ከዊነ፡ እሳት <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#150rb"/>
                           <desc type="PoemArke">A salām-hymn dedicated to ʾAragāwi Manfasāwi.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ እምብዝኃ፡ አንክሮ፡ ወተደሞ፨
                              ነጽሮተ፡ ሥሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ከመ፡ ማዕበለ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘያሠጥሞ፨ 
                              ሶበ፡ ኂርውናሁ፡ ነጸሩ፡ ወዘዚአሁ፡ አርምሞ፨
                              እንዘ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ያብጽሕ፡ ዓቅሞ፨ 
                              አረጋዊ፡ መንፈሳዊ፡ ሰመይዎ፡ ስሞ፨</q>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                             Hail to Yoḥannǝs from much of
                             admiration and wonder. Whom the vision of the Trinity submerged like a
                              wave of the sea. When they saw his benevolence and his quietness While
                              he was young and had not grown up yet He was called Spiritual
                              Elder.</quote>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#150rb"/>
                           <desc type="Poem">A poem dedicated to ʾAragāwi Manfasāwi.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ጳራቅሊጦስ፡ መንፈሰ፡ ትንቢት፡ ለናሆም፡ ዘሐወፆ፨
                              መጳራቅሊጦስ፡ መብረቅ፡ ለጳውሎስ፡ ዘአደንግፆ፨ መራኁተ፡ ስምዖን፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ጳራ፡ ፈታሔ፡ ማዕፆ፨ ለአረጋዊ፡
                              መንፈሳዊ፡ ያርኅወኒ፡ አንቀጾ፨ ስብሐተ፡ መልክዑ፡ እነጽር፡ ወፍሡሐ፡ ገጾ፨</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                             Paraclete, the Spirit of prophecy who visited Nāhom, Paraclete who terrified Paul with a
                              lightening, With the key of Simon Peter, the guardian of the gate,
                              Paraclete, May he open the gate for Spiritual Elder, So that I could
                              see his glorious appearance and his joyful face.</q>
                        </item>
                        
